OL,3,CWelsh Ambulance Service declares
OL,4,C"critical incident"
OL,6,F"We understand that this is
OL,7,Ffrustrating for patients, but can
OL,8,Fassure them that we are doing
OL,9,Feverything we can to relieve the
OL,10,Fpressure on our service.
OL,12,F"The public can help by only calling
OL,13,F999 in the event of a life-threatening
OL,14,Femergency - that's a cardiac arrest,
OL,15,Fchest pain or breathing difficulties,
OL,16,Floss of consciousness, choking or
OL,17,Fcatastrophic bleeding.
