OL,3,CWelsh Ambulance Service declares
OL,4,C"critical incident"
OL,6,F"If it's not a life-threatening
OL,7,Femergency, then it's important you use
OL,8,Fone of the many alternatives to 999,
OL,9,Fstarting with the symptom checkers on
OL,10,Four NHS 111 Wales website as well as
OL,11,Fyour GP, pharmacist and minor injuries
OL,12,Funit.
OL,14,F"We must protect our precious
OL,15,Fresources for those who need them the
OL,16,Fmost. Our staff and volunteers are
OL,17,Fdoing a brilliant job under difficult
OL,18,Fcircumstances, and we cannot thank
OL,19,Fthem enough for their hard work during
OL,20,Fthese very challenging times across
OL,21,Fthe health service."
